supportDesc.foliation:
Foliated to 105 in ink (s. xviii), rest of foliation is of s. s. xx. 
                           Medieval foliation, in arabic figures, in the same hand and position (on versos below first column) as in MS 13 (see our Pls. 1 and 2); 
                           the figures begin at 71 and continue to 177 on fol. 104v omitting 110 and losing 150 and 159 through the excision of leaves.
